**LANGUAGES-MANIFEST.md documents package manager manifest files across programming languages with support status flags for ARE's manifest detection logic.**

## Manifest Detection Matrix

References 24 programming language ecosystems with their manifest files used by `src/generation/prompts/builder.ts` during directory aggregation prompts. Columns define `Language`, `Manifest File(s)` (comma-separated multiple files for ecosystems with variants), `Package Manager` (toolchain names), and `Supported` (checkmark indicates ARE actively detects these manifests).

## Supported Manifests

ARE's `buildDirectoryPrompt()` in `src/generation/prompts/builder.ts` calls `detectManifests()` which checks for these marked-supported files:

- **JavaScript/TypeScript**: `package.json` (npm/yarn/pnpm)
- **Python**: `requirements.txt`, `pyproject.toml`, `setup.py`, `Pipfile` (pip/poetry/pipenv)
- **Go**: `go.mod` (go modules)
- **Rust**: `Cargo.toml` (cargo)

## Unsupported Manifests

Languages without checkmarks have detection stubs or are pending implementation:

- Ruby `Gemfile`, Java `pom.xml`/`build.gradle`, Kotlin `build.gradle.kts`, C# `*.csproj`, PHP `composer.json`, Swift `Package.swift`, Elixir `mix.exs`, Erlang `rebar.config`, Scala `build.sbt`, Clojure `deps.edn`/`project.clj`, Haskell `package.yaml`/`*.cabal`, Dart `pubspec.yaml`, Lua `*.rockspec`, R `DESCRIPTION`, Julia `Project.toml`, Zig `build.zig.zon`, Nim `*.nimble`, OCaml `dune-project`/`*.opam`, C/C++ `CMakeLists.txt`/`conanfile.txt`/`vcpkg.json`

## Integration Points

`src/generation/prompts/builder.ts` injects detected manifest metadata into directory aggregation prompts via `detectedManifests` array, enabling AI backends to infer dependency structure and entry points. Extension of manifest detection requires updating both this reference document and `detectManifests()` glob patterns.